        <h1>Ethical Considerations in IT</h1>
        <p>IT professionals must follow ethical guidelines to ensure responsible behavior in a digital world. For example:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Respect privacy and data confidentiality.</li>
            <li>Avoid bias in data-driven decisions (important for data scientists).</li>
            <li>Ensure transparency and honesty in software development.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>According to the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM), developers should <em>"contribute to society and to human well-being, acknowledging that all people are stakeholders in computing"</em> (ACM Code of Ethics, 2018).</p>
        <p><strong>Reference:</strong> Association for Computing Machinery. (2018). <em>ACM Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct</em>. https://www.acm.org/code-of-ethics</p>
    </main>
